{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_87","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"nl -ba docs/geometry_preview.md | sed -n '1,120p'\"","aggregated_output":"     1\t# Geometry Preview Workflow\n     2\t\n     3\tMilestone 5 preview generation is intentionally offline. The preview step reads\n     4\tonly local files that were already produced by the pipeline:\n     5\t\n     6\t- raw mesh: `config.paths.meshes_raw_dir/<root_id>.ply`\n     7\t- simplified mesh: `config.paths.processed_mesh_dir/<root_id>.ply`\n     8\t- optional skeleton: `config.paths.skeletons_raw_dir/<root_id>.swc`\n     9\t- surface graph: `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_graph.npz`\n    10\t- patch graph: `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_patch_graph.npz`\n    11\t- optional sidecars: descriptor and QA JSON written by `scripts/03_build_wave_assets.py`\n    12\t\n    13\t## Generate a preview\n    14\t\n    15\tPreview one or more specific root IDs:\n    16\t\n    17\t```bash\n    18\tpython scripts/05_preview_geometry.py --config config/local.yaml --root-id 101 --root-id 102\n    19\t```\n    20\t\n    21\tPreview the active selected subset from `config.paths.selected_root_ids`:\n    22\t\n    23\t```bash\n    24\tpython scripts/05_preview_geometry.py --config config/local.yaml --limit 4\n    25\t```\n    26\t\n    27\tEquivalent Make target:\n    28\t\n    29\t```bash\n    30\tmake preview CONFIG=config/local.yaml\n    31\t```\n    32\t\n    33\tThe output location is deterministic for the exact root-id set. By default the\n    34\tscript writes to:\n    35\t\n    36\t```text\n    37\tconfig.paths.geometry_preview_dir/root-ids-<sorted-root-ids>/\n    38\t```\n    39\t\n    40\tExample:\n    41\t\n    42\t```text\n    43\tdata/processed/previews/root-ids-101-102/index.html\n    44\tdata/processed/previews/root-ids-101-102/summary.json\n    45\tdata/processed/previews/root-ids-101-102/root_ids.txt\n    46\t```\n    47\t\n    48\tThat makes the report path stable enough to reference from run logs, ticket\n    49\tnotes, or review comments.\n    50\t\n    51\tIf one or more required preview inputs are missing, the command still writes the\n    52\tdeterministic preview directory and returns a structured blocked summary instead\n    53\tof aborting on the first `FileNotFoundError`. The summary records the blocked\n    54\troot IDs, missing asset keys, resolved paths, and whether the operator should\n    55\trerun `make meshes`, `make assets`, or both.\n    56\t\n    57\t## What the report shows\n    58\t\n    59\tEach root section keeps the following in one place:\n    60\t\n    61\t- raw mesh wireframe\n    62\t- simplified mesh wireframe\n    63\t- skeleton projection or an explicit unavailable marker\n    64\t- surface graph projection\n    65\t- patch graph projection\n    66\t- bundle summary metrics, artifact paths, and QA highlights\n    67\t\n    68\tThe HTML is fully static and does not require a notebook server, Neuroglancer,\n    69\tor FlyWire access.\n    70\t\n    71\t## Reviewer checklist\n    72\t\n    73\tReviewers should look for:\n    74\t\n    75\t- raw vs simplified mesh silhouette staying broadly consistent rather than collapsing or drifting\n    76\t- skeleton presence matching expectations for that neuron and following the same gross orientation as the meshes when available\n    77\t- surface graph coverage matching the simplified geometry instead of showing obvious holes or disconnected clutter\n    78\t- patch graph being non-empty and spatially distributed rather than collapsing to one dominant patch unless that is expected\n    79\t- QA warnings or failures that suggest simplification drift, patch coverage gaps, or coarse graph degeneracy\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
